{"title":"Final Fantasy VII Remake Intergrade leads latest PlayStation game-reveal event","link":"https://arstechnica.com/?p=1745306","date":1614296713000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><header><h4>Fix the door texture, please —</h4><h2 itemprop=\"description\">Plus, closer looks at <em>Deathloop</em>, <em>Returnal</em>, <em>Solar Ash</em>, more.</h2></header><div itemprop=\"articleBody\"><div><ul><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2326-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2326.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2326-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2326-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745381\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745381\"><span></span><p>Yuffie—a beloved hero who is in the original <em>Final Fantasy VII</em> but not its existing remake—returns to the remake's... remake.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2260-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2260.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2260-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2260-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745384\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745384\"><span></span><p>Yuffie in a Moogle suit!</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2271-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2271.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2271-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2271-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745383\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745383\"><span></span><p>Yuffie removes her Moogle hood so as to better examine some Materia.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2324-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2324.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2324-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2324-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745382\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745382\"><span></span><p>Yuffie leaps off of her battling partner's blade to dive-attack a foe.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2411-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2411.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2411-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2411-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745374\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745374\"><span></span><p>Iconic weaponry returns.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2425-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2425.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2425-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2425-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745373\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745373\"><span></span><p>Everything you're curious about... except for the episode's standalone price, which we still don't know.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2394-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2394.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2394-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2394-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745375\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745375\"><span></span><p>How \"classic\" mode works in normal difficulty.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2388-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2388.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2388-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2388-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745376\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745376\"><span></span><p>Higher-fidelity hair for all of Cloud's stans.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2385-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2385.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2385-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2385-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745377\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745377\"><span></span><p>We doubt that this new reflective-glass effect is based on ray tracing, but it's a handsome update all the same.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2382-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2382.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2382-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2382-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745378\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745378\"><span></span><p>Dynamic lighting gets a PS5 overhaul.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2365-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2365.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2365-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2365-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745379\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745379\"><span></span><p>I mean, I guess they look sharper? Kind of?</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2360-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2360.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2360-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2360-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745380\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745380\"><span></span><p>Since the video feed was only 1080p resolution, this tease of higher-resolution textures wasn't very clear.</p><p><span></span> Square Enix</p></figcaption></figure></li></ul></div><p>Sony's latest PlayStation-focused video reveal event, as part of its State Of Play series, was its shortest yet, lacking announcements on&nbsp;any first-party Sony games coming to either PlayStation 5 or the older PS4. Instead, the event was led by a third-party whopper: a remake of... <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2020/04/final-fantasy-vii-remake-spoiler-free-review-our-kind-of-cloud-gaming/\">last year's <em>Final Fantasy VII Remake</em></a>.</p><p>That definition is a stretch, since this new title may be better classified as a graphical remaster, but there's a lot going on, as visible in the above gallery. The new game, <em>FFVII Remake Intergrade</em>, will land exclusively on PlayStation 5 consoles on June 10, and in good news, existing owners on PS4 will get nearly all of its content as a free upgrade (so long as they either own the game digitally or have a disc-based PS5). That content includes a sweeping graphical overhaul with new lighting, texture, and particle systems and an optional 60fps mode, plus a new \"classic\" option for the game's active battling system. Picking \"classic\" will let players focus entirely on selecting commands from menus, instead of giving direct joystick control to a \"lead\" character like Cloud or Tifa.</p><p>For existing owners who may have already beaten the game, the incentive to double-dip comes in the form of a new \"episode\" of content. This will put players in control of original series character Yuffie, and the revealed footage includes her and a companion named Sonon spending time in existing game regions like the Sector 7 slums—and Yuffie using Sonon as a springboard to pull off cinematic, sweeping attacks. To access this new chapter, existing owners will have to pay for the extra DLC, though publisher Square Enix hasn't yet clarified how much that will cost.</p><div><ul><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1907-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1907.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1907-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1907-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745330\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745330\"><span></span><p>Pew pew! <em>Returnal</em> looks satisfyingly action-packed, but whether it stands out in the modern roguelike fray remains to be seen.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1928-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1928.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1928-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1928-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745329\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745329\"><span></span><p>Creative, over-the-top weaponry abounds in <em>Returnal</em>.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1899-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1899.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1899-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1899-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745333\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745333\"><span></span><p>Dash-dodging in <em>Returnal</em>.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1901-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1901.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1901-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1901-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745332\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745332\"><span></span><p>Blowing things up real good in <em>Returnal</em>.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1913-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1913.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1913-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1913-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745331\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745331\"><span></span><p>The kinds of sparkly combat effects we expect from the devs at Housemarque.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1937-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1937.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1937-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1937-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745328\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745328\"><span></span><p>Stick hand in goo, get stronger. You know the gaming drill.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1950-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1950.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1950-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1950-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745326\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745326\"><span></span><p>A brief look at first-person exploration in one plot-filled sequence.</p></figcaption></figure></li></ul></div><p>The closest Thursday's event got to a \"first-party\" reveal came from <em>Returnal</em>, a second-party project by longtime Sony collaborator Housemarque. We finally learned that the game is launching April 30—and saw the clearest footage yet of its roguelike action. This third-person shooter largely resembles <em>Risk of Rain 2</em>, in terms of pitting players against fantastical, supernatural beasts while letting players access a mix of wild attacks and high-speed dodges. (Though unlike RoR2, Returnal appears to be a single-player affair.) Thursday's trailer also gave us a peek at a plot tying the game's \"die-and-retry\" roguelike loop together, which included a look at the main character's childhood home (which players could discover and explore in a first-person perspective).</p><div><ul><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2028-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2028.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2028-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2028-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745345\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745345\"><span></span><p><em>Solar Ash</em> stars this stylistically rendered hero, who leaps, runs, and battles through a world that looks like the cover of a '70s sci-fi novel.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1998-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1998.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1998-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-1998-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745347\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745347\"><span></span><p>Solar Ash's blurry, high-speed trailer barely paused to let us reflect on its beauty.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2018-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2018.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2018-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2018-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745346\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745346\"><span></span><p>Leaping across a boss in Solar Ash.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2035-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2035.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2035-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2035-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745343\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745343\"><span></span><p>Clambering across a boss's back.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2046-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2046.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2046-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2046-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745341\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745341\"><span></span><p>We gotta climb on top of <em>that</em> thing?!</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2000-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2000.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2000-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2000-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745348\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745348\"><span></span><p>They've arrived.</p></figcaption></figure></li></ul></div><p><em>Solar Ash</em>, which was revealed during Sony's last State of Play presentation, will arrive \"later this year\" from the team behind beloved indie action game <em>Hyper Light Drifter</em>, and we finally got a firm look at this PlayStation console exclusive's gameplay. The results look like a cross between <em>Jet Set Radio</em> and <em>Shadow of the Colossus</em>, in terms of high-speed third-person platforming combined with epic \"crawl over bosses\" encounters.</p><div><ul><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2104-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2104.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2104-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2104-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745393\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745393\"><span></span><p>Use gadgets built into your arms to take out foes in <em>Deathloop</em>.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2108-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2108.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2108-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2108-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745392\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745392\"><span></span><p>It's hard to see, but that's a knife blade turned translucent by mystical abilities in <em>Deathloop</em>.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2140-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2140.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2140-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2140-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745391\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745391\"><span></span><p>First-person combat in <em>Deathloop</em>.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2098-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2098.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2098-980x551.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Screenshot-2098-1440x810.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1745395\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1745395\"><span></span><p>This in-game shot of <em>Deathloop</em> looks like something out of a film trailer.</p></figcaption></figure></li></ul></div><p>The PlayStation console exclusive shooter <em>Deathloop</em> received its first hard gameplay reveal on Thursday, as well, and it finally looks like an Arkane Lyon game—meaning, it now resembles its <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2016/11/dishonored-2-review/\"><em>Dishonored</em></a> first-person-stealth pedigree. Only, imagine that kind of gameplay supercharged with supernatural powers (invisibility, stealth, and magical attacks), 007-styled gadgets, and the tongue-in-cheek, '70s-technicolor-spy gaming glory of <em>No One Lives Forever</em>. That combination of influences has us excited for what's to come from this Bethesda-published game (which Sony nabbed before <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2020/09/microsoft-purchases-bethesda-softworks-in-industry-changing-acquisition\">that Microsoft acquisition deal</a>), but we're still waiting on its release date.</p><p>Unfortunately, the highly anticipated video event was utterly bereft of first-party announcements, thus leaving fans in the dark about June's <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2020/08/incredible-ratchet-clank-gameplay-demo-reveals-the-playstation-5-difference/\"><em>Ratchet and Clank</em> sequel</a>, let alone sequels to <em>Gran Turismo</em>, <em>God of War</em>, and <em>Horizon: Zero Dawn</em>. For the rest of the event's announcements and teases, which included a firmer look at upcoming PlayStation 4/5 games <em>Oddworld Soulstorm</em> and <em>Kena: Bridge of Spirits</em>, check out the full 30-minute video, embedded below.</p><figure><p><iframe type=\"text/html\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tuJqHuANkyw?start=0&amp;wmode=transparent\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p><figcaption><p>Sony State of Play, February 25, 2021</p></figcaption></figure><p><em>Listing image by Square Enix</em></p></div></div></div>","author":"Sam Machkovech","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"ab2594f731f7f2d11f191f1f2b83637d5633f287a33f9a82b533c4eee4767288","category":"Tech"}